## Security Best Practices

### 1. Token Management

- ✅ Tokens expire after 5 minutes

- ✅ Tokens are signed with HMAC-SHA256

- ✅ Tokens include agent integrity hash

- ✅ Tokens can be revoked immediately

- ✅ All token issuance logged

### 2. Agent Verification

- ✅ Agent identity verified before token issuance

- ✅ Agent compromise status checked

- ✅ Agent permissions checked against matrix

- ✅ Agent integrity hash verified

### 3. Brain Access

- ✅ All access requires valid token

- ✅ Token verified before allowing access

- ✅ Agent re-verified not compromised

- ✅ All access logged to audit trail

### 4. Owner Controls

- ✅ Owner has full access to all brains

- ✅ Owner can revoke any token

- ✅ Owner can mark agent as compromised

- ✅ Owner can view complete audit log

- ✅ Owner has emergency kill switch

### 5. Audit Logging

- ✅ Every token request logged

- ✅ Every brain access logged

- ✅ Every access denial logged

- ✅ Logs include timestamp, agent, action, result

- ✅ Logs immutable and tamper-proof

